## Why This Is Asked

This question evaluates a candidate's ability to design safe, scalable chaos experiments for multi-region, real-time systems with precise blast radius control and explicit recovery criteria. Strong answers demonstrate experience with distributed systems resilience patterns and operational maturity.

## Key Concepts

- Chaos experiments with blast radius and safety constraints
- Multi-region latency, replication lag, and data integrity
- Circuit breakers, backpressure, and local message buffering
- Canary deployments with automated rollback criteria
- Telemetry: RED metrics (Rate, Errors, Duration), p95 latency thresholds, error budgets, and distributed tracing

## Code Example

```javascript
class CircuitBreaker {
  constructor(threshold, timeout) {
    this.failures = 0;
    this.threshold = threshold;
    this.timeout = timeout;
    this.state = 'CLOSED';
    this.lastFailure = null;
  }

  recordFailure() {
    this.failures++;
    this.lastFailure = Date.now();
    if (this.failures >= this.threshold) {
      this.state = 'OPEN';
      setTimeout(() => this.state = 'HALF-OPEN', this.timeout);
    }
  }

  recordSuccess() {
    this.failures = 0;
    this.state = 'CLOSED';
  }

  canExecute() {
    return this.state !== 'OPEN';
  }
}
```
